{"title_page": "Canadian Emergency Wage Subsidy", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2020}}\nThe '''Canadian Emergency Wage Subsidy''' ('''CEWS''') is a Canadian support program created by the [[Government of Canada]].<ref name=\"gm3br\">{{cite news |title=The three bridges Canada needs to get us across the economic chasm |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/opinion/editorials/article-the-three-bridges-canada-needs-to-get-us-across-the-economic-chasm/ |publisher=The Globe and Mail Inc |date=13 April 2020}}</ref> The program was launched on 11 April 2020, upon passage of Bill C-XXX, for Canadian residents facing [[layoffs]] due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Canada|2020 coronavirus pandemic]].\n\nFor example, [[Air Canada]] announced because of the CEWS it would re-hire backdated to 15 March 16,000 airline staff that were laid off due to the pandemic.<ref name=\"gm3br\"/> The CEWS is targeted \"at businesses with [[revenue]] declines of at least 15 per cent in March, and 30 per cent in May and June.\"<ref name=\"gm3br\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Government in Canada]]\n[[Category:Canadian society]]\n[[Category:Social programs]]\n[[Category:Social security in Canada]]\n[[Category:Unemployment benefits]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Canada]]\n[[Category:National responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n\n{{Canada-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2020}}\nThe '''Canadian Emergency Wage Subsidy''' ('''CEWS''') is a Canadian support program created by the [[Government of Canada]].<ref name=\"gm3br\">{{cite news |title=The three bridges Canada needs to get us across the economic chasm |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/opinion/editorials/article-the-three-bridges-canada-needs-to-get-us-across-the-economic-chasm/ |publisher=The Globe and Mail Inc |date=13 April 2020}}</ref> The program was launched on 11 April 2020, upon passage of Bill C-XXX, for Canadian residents facing [[layoffs]] due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Canada|2020 coronavirus pandemic]].\n\nFor example, [[Air Canada]] announced because of the CEWS it would re-hire backdated to 15 March 16,000 airline staff that were laid off due to the pandemic.<ref name=\"gm3br\"/> The CEWS is targetted \"at businesses with [[revenue]] declines of at least 15 per cent in March, and 30 per cent in May and June.\"<ref name=\"gm3br\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Government in Canada]]\n[[Category:Canadian society]]\n[[Category:Social programs]]\n[[Category:Social security in Canada]]\n[[Category:Unemployment benefits]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Canada]]\n[[Category:National responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n\n{{Canada-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: targetted \u2192 targeted", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canadian_Emergency_Wage_Subsidy"}
