{"title_page": "Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name         = Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato\n| image        = Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato.png\n| caption      = Malato in 2015\n| birth_name   = Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1964|03|07|df=y}}\n| birth_place  = [[Monforte Municipality|Monforte]], Portugal\n| nationality  = [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]]\n| occupation   = [[Television presenter]]\n| known_for    =\n| partner      =\n| years_active = 1984\u2013present\n| parents      =\n| children     =\n| website      =\n}}\n\n'''Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato''' (born 7 March 1964, in [[Monforte Municipality|Monforte]]<ref>{{IMDB name|2120151|Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato}}</ref>) is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] [[TV]] presenter, radio broadcaster, [[copywriter]] and college teacher.<ref>[http://ww1.rtp.pt/wportal/sites/tv/jogo_duplo/apresentador.php Jogo Duplo \u00bb Apresentador] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100329061433/http://ww1.rtp.pt/wportal/sites/tv/jogo_duplo/apresentador.php |date=29 March 2010 }}, in Portuguese</ref> In 2018, he publicly announced that he is gay.<ref>https://www.n-tv.pt/rosa-choque/malato-assume-homossexualidade-apos-morte-do-pai-onde-estiver-compreendera-todas-as-dimensoes-da-palavra-amor/</ref>\n\n==Television programs hosted==\n* ''Top+'', on [[RTP1]] with [[Ana Lamy]].\n* ''Portugal no Cora\u00e7\u00e3o'', on RTP1, with [[Merche Romero]], [[Marta Leite de Castro]] and [[Cristina Alves]].\n* ''[[1 vs. 100|Um Contra Todos]]'', on RTP1.\n* ''A Heran\u00e7a'', on RTP1.\n* ''Sexta \u00c0 Noite'', on RTP1.\n* ''[[PokerFace (game show)|Jogo Duplo]]'', on RTP1.\n* ''Decis\u00e3o Final'', on RTP1.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.facebook.com/josecarlosmalato Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato's Facebook]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Malato, Jose Carlos}}\n[[Category:Portuguese television presenters]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Portugal]]\n\n\n{{Tv-bio-stub}}\n{{portugal-tv-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name       = Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato\n| image      = Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato.png\n| caption    = Malato in 2015\n| birth_name  = Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1964|03|07|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Monforte Municipality|Monforte]], Portugal\n| nationality = [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]]\n| occupation = [[Television presenter]]\n| known_for  =\n| partner =\n| years_active = 1984\u2013present\n| parents =\n| children =\n| website =\n}}\n\n'''Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato''' (born 7 March 1964, in [[Monforte Municipality|Monforte]]<ref>{{IMDB name|2120151|Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato}}</ref>) is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] [[TV]] presenter, radio broadcaster, [[copywriter]] and college teacher.<ref>[http://ww1.rtp.pt/wportal/sites/tv/jogo_duplo/apresentador.php Jogo Duplo \u00bb Apresentador] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100329061433/http://ww1.rtp.pt/wportal/sites/tv/jogo_duplo/apresentador.php |date=29 March 2010 }}, in Portuguese</ref> In 2018, he publicly announced that he is gay.<ref>https://www.n-tv.pt/rosa-choque/malato-assume-homossexualidade-apos-morte-do-pai-onde-estiver-compreendera-todas-as-dimensoes-da-palavra-amor/</ref>\n\n==TV programs hosted==\n* ''Top+'', on [[RTP1]] with [[Ana Lamy]].\n* ''Portugal no Cora\u00e7\u00e3o'', on RTP1, with [[Merche Romero]], [[Marta Leite de Castro]] and [[Cristina Alves]].\n* ''[[1 vs. 100|Um Contra Todos]]'', on RTP1.\n* ''A Heran\u00e7a'', on RTP1.\n* ''Sexta \u00c0 Noite'', on RTP1.\n* ''[[PokerFace (game show)|Jogo Duplo]]'', on RTP1.\n* ''Decis\u00e3o Final'', on RTP1.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.facebook.com/josecarlosmalato Jos\u00e9 Carlos Malato's Facebook]\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Malato, Jose Carlos}}\n[[Category:Portuguese television presenters]]\n